üìñ The Story of Ash

The Ash flows through the Upper Lea (Hertfordshire) catchment, where our eDNA survey sampled 7 sites along its length. Analysis of water samples revealed a rich invertebrate community with 4,474 distinct genetic sequences (ESVs) representing 583 identified species and 237 families.

Compared to other chalk streams surveyed, the Ash shows moderate diversity compared to other rivers in the study (#8 of 10). The river supports 14 families of mayflies, stoneflies, and caddisflies (EPT) - key indicators of water quality.

Notable findings include the detection of conservation priority species (Water vole, Water shrew) and invasive species requiring management attention.
